 </disp-formula> where RFC
 <sub>s(max)</sub> is the relative frequency of citation over the maximum, i.e., and was measured with FCs divided by the maximum value in all the species of the survey. RNU
 <sub>s</sub> is the relative number of use-categories over the maximum and it was calculated with the number of uses of the species (NU
 <sub>s</sub>) divided by the maximum value in survey
